how do add a subdomain under my hosting website?

To add a subdomain under your hosting website, you'll typically need to log into your hosting provider's control panel. Look for the 'Domains' section and find an option to create a new subdomain. Enter the name of the subdomain you want to create and link it to the appropriate directory on your server. If you're unsure, it's best to check with your specific hosting provider's support or documentation for detailed instructions.
